= Setup

- *Hardware.* Raspberry Pi Pico 2 W (RP2350, ARM Cortex-M33 @ 150 MHz
  and Hazard3 RV32 @ 150 MHz; 520 KB SRAM).
- *Verifier.* `zkmcu-verifier` 0.1.0, `no_std`, EIP-197 wire format,
  `substrate-bn` 0.6 as the crypto backend. Unchanged from earlier
  phase-2.0–2.6 runs.
- *Firmware.* `bench-rp2350-m33` / `bench-rp2350-rv32`, extended in
  commit `5aeadb9` to bench the Semaphore vector alongside `square` +
  `squares-5`.
- *Vector provenance.* VK from `vendor/semaphore/packages/proof/src/
  verification-keys.json` (depth 10 slice). Proof from
  `scripts/gen-semaphore-proof/` running
  `@semaphore-protocol/proof` 4.14.2 under
  `snark-artifacts` tag 4.13.0. Deterministic under the hardcoded
  seed `"zkmcu-bench-seed"` + message `"zkmcu-bench-message"` +
  scope `"zkmcu-bench-scope"`, so the vector is byte-identical on
  every regeneration.
- *Toolchain.* `rustc 1.94.1`, `release` profile with `lto = "fat"`,
  `opt-level = "s"`, `codegen-units = 1`, `panic = "abort"`.
- *Measurement.* `DWT::cycle_count` on Cortex-M33, `mcycle` on
  Hazard3 (with `mcountinhibit` unmasked at boot per phase-0 finding).

